Agriculture stakeholders should partner with varsities to improve farming methods, University of Eldoret chancellor Judith Bahemuka has said.Speaking when she closed a three-day agribusiness trade fair at the university on Saturday, she said, &ldquo;We have contributed to the growth of the agriculture sector through research and training of agricultural professionals.&rdquo;Bahemuka urged stakeholders not to work in isolation. &ldquo;This will only make the situation worse,&rdquo; she said.Exhibitors included farm input suppliers, seed, fertiliser, fish farming and crop machinery companies.The theme of this year&rsquo;s fair was &lsquo;Towards Food Security and National Growth through Agricultural Innovation and Technology Transfer.&rsquo;